[2026-03-13T14:37:10Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SEaM7nVhnav3GaFNSLiFDN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Cloche Usage\n     2→\n     3→Cloche runs containerized workflows for autonomous coding agents. You define a\n     4→workflow graph in the `.cloche` DSL, Cloche copies your project into a Docker\n     5→container, runs the workflow steps (agent prompts and shell scripts), and extracts\n     6→results to a git branch.\n     7→\n     8→## Core Concepts\n     9→\n    10→- **Workflow**: A directed graph of steps connected by named-result wiring.\n    11→- **Step**: A unit of work. Type is inferred: `prompt` = agent step, `run` = script step, `workflow_name` = workflow step (host only).\n    12→- **Result**: A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. `success`, `fail`, `needs-research`). Steps declare their possible results; the engine follows wiring based on the reported result.\n    13→- **Wiring**: Maps `step:result` pairs to the next step. Separate from step definitions.\n    14→- **Terminals**: `done` (success) and `abort` (failure) are built-in terminal targets.\n    15→\n    16→## Workflow DSL\n    17→\n    18→Workflow files use the `.cloche` extension and live in `.cloche/`. The first step\n    19→declared is the entry point. Graphs are validated at parse time (all results wired,\n    20→no orphans, entry point exists).\n    21→\n    22→### Minimal Example\n    23→\n    24→```\n    25→workflow \"develop\" {\n    26→  step implement {\n    27→    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    28→    results = [success, fail]\n    29→  }\n    30→\n    31→  step test {\n    32→    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    33→    results = [success, fail]\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  implement:success -> test\n    37→  implement:fail -> abort\n    38→  test:success -> done\n    39→  test:fail -> abort\n    40→}\n    41→```\n    42→\n    43→### Step Configuration\n    44→\n    45→| Key | Type | Description |\n    46→|-----|------|-------------|\n    47→| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | Prompt template. Makes this an agent step. |\n    48→| `run` | string | Shell command. Makes this a script step. |\n    49→| `workflow_name` | string | Container workflow to dispatch. Makes this a workflow step (host only). |\n    50→| `results` | ident list | Declared result names, e.g. `[success, fail, give-up]`. |\n    51→| `max_attempts` | string | Max retries before automatic `give-up` result, e.g. `\"2\"`. |\n    52→| `timeout` | string | Step timeout as Go duration, e.g. `\"30m\"`, `\"2h\"`. Default: 30m. |\n    53→| `agent_command` | string | Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback chains, e.g. `\"claude,gemini\"`. |\n    54→| `agent_args` | string | Override default agent arguments. |\n    55→| `feedback` | string | Set to `\"true\"` to include `.cloche/output/*.log` content in the prompt. |\n    56→| `prompt_step` | string | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as the prompt. |\n    57→\n    58→A step must have exactly one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`.\n    59→\n    60→### The `file()` Function\n    61→\n    62→`file(\"path\")` reads the file at the given path relative to the working directory\n    63→(`/workspace/` in containers) at execution time, not parse time. Use it for prompt\n    64→templates:\n    65→\n    66→```\n    67→prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    68→```\n    69→\n    70→### The `container {}` Block\n    71→\n    72→Can appear at step level or workflow level. Keys are stored with a `container.` prefix.\n    73→\n    74→**Step level** — per-step container config:\n    75→```\n    76→step code {\n    77→  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    78→  container {\n    79→    image         = \"custom-agent:v2\"\n    80→    memory        = \"4g\"\n    81→    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n    82→  }\n    83→  results = [success, fail]\n    84→}\n    85→```\n    86→\n    87→**Workflow level** — defaults for all steps:\n    88→```\n    89→workflow \"develop\" {\n    90→  container {\n    91→    agent_command = \"gemini\"\n    92→    image         = \"myregistry/myimage:v2\"\n    93→    memory        = \"4g\"\n    94→  }\n    95→  ...\n    96→}\n    97→```\n    98→\n    99→Supported keys: `image`, `memory`, `network_allow`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`.\n   100→\n   101→### The `host {}` Block\n   102→\n   103→Can appear at workflow level in host workflows (`.cloche/host.cloche`). Keys are stored\n   104→with a `host.` prefix. Configures agent defaults for agent steps running on the host.\n   105→\n   106→```\n   107→workflow \"main\" {\n   108→  host {\n   109→    agent_command = \"claude\"\n   110→  }\n   111→  ...\n   112→}\n   113→```\n   114→\n   115→Supported keys: `agent_command`, `agent_args`. Step-level `agent_command` and\n   116→`agent_args` config keys override the workflow-level `host {}` defaults.\n   117→\n   118→### Wiring Syntax\n   119→\n   120→Connect steps with `step:result -> next_step`:\n   121→\n   122→```\n   123→implement:success -> test\n   124→implement:fail -> abort\n   125→test:success -> done\n   126→test:fail -> fix\n   127→```\n   128→\n   129→### Wire Output Mappings\n   130→\n   131→Extract values from a step's JSON output and inject as env vars into the target:\n   132→\n   133→```\n   134→step-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n   135→```\n   136→\n   137→Path expressions:\n   138→\n   139→| Expression | Meaning |\n   140→|---|---|\n   141→| `output` | Raw output (full string) |\n   142→| `output.key` | JSON object field access |\n   143→| `output[N]` | JSON array index (0-based) |\n   144→| `output.a.b.c` | Deeply nested field access |\n   145→| `output.items[0].name` | Mixed field and index chaining |\n   146→\n   147→If the output is valid JSON, path expressions navigate the structure. If it's plain\n   148→text, only bare `output` works.\n   149→\n   150→### Retry Loops\n   151→\n   152→Wire failures back to earlier steps:\n   153→\n   154→```\n   155→test:fail -> fix\n   156→fix:success -> test    // retry the test\n   157→fix:fail -> abort\n   158→```\n   159→\n   160→Use `max_attempts` to cap retries. When exhausted, the step returns `give-up`:\n   161→\n   162→```\n   163→step fix {\n   164→  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n   165→  max_attempts = \"2\"\n   166→  results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   167→}\n   168→```\n   169→\n   170→### Parallel Branches (Fanout)\n   171→\n   172→Wire one result to multiple targets for concurrent execution:\n   173→\n   174→```\n   175→test:success -> lint\n   176→test:success -> quality\n   177→```\n   178→\n   179→### Collect (Join)\n   180→\n   181→Synchronize parallel branches:\n   182→\n   183→```\n   184→collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   185→collect any(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   186→```\n   187→\n   188→`all` fires when every condition is met. `any` fires when at least one is.\n   189→\n   190→### Comments\n   191→\n   192→Line comments with `//`:\n   193→\n   194→```\n   195→// This is a comment\n   196→implement:success -> test  // inline comment\n   197→```\n   198→\n   199→## Result Protocol\n   200→\n   201→Steps report results by printing a marker line to stdout:\n   202→\n   203→```\n   204→CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\n   205→```\n   206→\n   207→For example: `CLOCHE_RESULT:success`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:needs-research`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:give-up`.\n   208→\n   209→Rules:\n   210→- The **last** `CLOCHE_RESULT:` line wins if multiple are printed.\n   211→- Marker lines are **stripped** from captured output (not passed to logs or downstream steps).\n   212→- The result name must match one of the step's declared `results`.\n   213→- For script steps with no marker: exit 0 = `success`, exit non-zero = `fail`.\n   214→- For agent steps: if exit non-zero with a marker, the marker result is used. If exit non-zero without a marker, falls back to the next agent in the fallback chain (or returns `fail` if last).\n   215→\n   216→## Prompt Assembly\n   217→\n   218→When an agent step runs, Cloche assembles a prompt from these sections (joined by blank lines):\n   219→\n   220→1. **Step template**: The step's `prompt` content (inline string or resolved `file(\"path\")`).\n   221→2. **User request**: Content of `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` (set via `--prompt` flag), prefixed with `## User Request`.\n   222→3. **Validation output** (opt-in): If `feedback = \"true\"`, reads all `.log` files from `.cloche/output/` and includes them prefixed with `## Validation Output`.\n   223→4. **Result selection**: Lists the step's declared results with instructions to print exactly one `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker.\n   224→\n   225→The assembled prompt is passed to the agent command via stdin.\n   226→\n   227→## Agent Command Resolution\n   228→\n   229→Priority (highest to lowest):\n   230→1. Step-level `agent_command`\n   231→2. Workflow-level config block (`container { agent_command }` for container workflows, `host { agent_command }` for host workflows)\n   232→3. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable\n   233→4. Default: `claude`\n   234→\n   235→### Fallback Chains\n   236→\n   237→Comma-separated commands are tried in order:\n   238→\n   239→```\n   240→agent_command = \"claude,gemini,codex\"\n   241→```\n   242→\n   243→- **Command not found / failed to start** — try next command\n   244→- **Exit non-zero without `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** — try next command\n   245→- **Exit non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** — use that result (no fallback)\n   246→- **Exit 0** — use result (no fallback)\n   247→- **All commands fail to start** — step returns an error\n   248→- **Last command crashes without marker** — step returns `fail`\n   249→\n   250→Known agents (e.g. `claude`) get default arguments (`-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions`). Unknown agents receive the prompt on stdin with no flags. Override with `agent_args`.\n   251→\n   252→## Workflow Locations\n   253→\n   254→**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) run inside Docker\n   255→via `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type.\n   256→\n   257→**Host workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) runs on the host machine as the daemon.\n   258→Steps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow_name` step type\n   259→dispatches a container workflow run and blocks until it completes. Script steps\n   260→execute with their working directory set to the main git worktree, so host-workflow\n   261→fixes on main are available to in-flight runs even if they branched earlier.\n   262→\n   263→A single `host.cloche` file may contain **multiple named workflows**. The daemon\n   264→uses up to three workflow phases for orchestration:\n   265→\n   266→| Phase | Workflow name | Purpose |\n   267→|-------|--------------|---------|\n   268→| 1 | `list-tasks` | Discover available work. Output is JSONL (one task per line). |\n   269→| 2 | `main` | Do the work. Receives a task ID via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var. |\n   270→| 3 | `finalize` | Post-main cleanup. Runs on **both** success and failure. |\n   271→\n   272→Only `main` is required. If `list-tasks` is absent, the daemon uses a single-workflow\n   273→mode. If `finalize` is absent, it is skipped.\n   274→\n   275→### list-tasks Output Format\n   276→\n   277→The `list-tasks` workflow's final step output is parsed as JSONL. Each line is a JSON\n   278→object:\n   279→\n   280→| Field | Required | Description |\n   281→|-------|----------|-------------|\n   282→| `id` | yes | Unique task identifier |\n   283→| `status` | yes | One of `open`, `closed`, `in-progress` |\n   284→| `title` | no | Short summary |\n   285→| `description` | no | Full description |\n   286→| `metadata` | no | Arbitrary key-value pairs |\n   287→\n   288→The daemon picks the first task with status `open`, runs `main` with that task's ID\n   289→set in `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`, then runs `finalize` with the outcome. Tasks are\n   290→deduplicated within a timeout window to prevent rapid reassignment of the same task.\n   291→\n   292→### Host Workflow Example\n   293→\n   294→A three-phase `host.cloche`:\n   295→\n   296→```\n   297→workflow \"list-tasks\" {\n   298→  step fetch-tickets {\n   299→    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh\"\n   300→    results = [success, fail]\n   301→  }\n   302→\n   303→  fetch-tickets:success -> done\n   304→  fetch-tickets:fail    -> abort\n   305→}\n   306→\n   307→workflow \"main\" {\n   308→  host {\n   309→    agent_command = \"claude\"\n   310→  }\n   311→\n   312→  step prepare-prompt {\n   313→    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n   314→    results = [success, fail]\n   315→  }\n   316→\n   317→  step develop {\n   318→    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n   319→    results       = [success, fail]\n   320→  }\n   321→\n   322→  prepare-prompt:success -> develop\n   323→  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n   324→  develop:success        -> done\n   325→  develop:fail           -> done\n   326→}\n   327→\n   328→workflow \"finalize\" {\n   329→  step push-for-review {\n   330→    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/push-for-review.sh\"\n   331→    results = [success, fail]\n   332→  }\n   333→\n   334→  push-for-review:success -> done\n   335→  push-for-review:fail    -> done\n   336→}\n   337→```\n   338→\n   339→The `list-tasks` script writes JSONL to `$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`. The `main` workflow\n   340→receives the task ID and is responsible for claiming the ticket. The `finalize`\n   341→workflow receives `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` and `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` env vars to decide\n   342→what cleanup to perform.\n   343→\n   344→### Host Step Environment Variables\n   345→\n   346→| Variable | Description |\n   347→|----------|-------------|\n   348→| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Absolute path to the project directory on the host. |\n   349→| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Path where this step should write its output (for output mappings). |\n   350→| `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` | Path to the output file from the immediately preceding step. |\n   351→| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n   352→| `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` | Task ID assigned by the daemon (set for `main` and `finalize` phases). |\n   353→| `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` | Result of the `main` workflow (`succeeded` or `failed`). Set for `finalize` phase only. |\n   354→| `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` | Run ID of the completed `main` workflow. Set for `finalize` phase only. |\n   355→| Wire-mapped vars | Any env vars declared in wire output mappings. |\n   356→\n   357→### Container Environment Variables\n   358→\n   359→| Variable | Description |\n   360→|----------|-------------|\n   361→| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n   362→| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Working directory (set for script steps so `cloche get`/`cloche set` work). |\n   363→| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Passed through from the host if set. |\n   364→| `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` | Overrides the default agent command inside the container. |\n   365→\n   366→## Complete Example: Container Workflow with Parallel Validation\n   367→\n   368→```\n   369→workflow \"develop\" {\n   370→  step implement {\n   371→    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n   372→    results = [success, fail]\n   373→  }\n   374→\n   375→  step test {\n   376→    run = \"bundle exec rake test 2>&1\"\n   377→    results = [success, fail]\n   378→  }\n   379→\n   380→  step lint {\n   381→    run = \"bundle exec rubocop 2>&1\"\n   382→    results = [success, fail]\n   383→  }\n   384→\n   385→  step quality {\n   386→    run = \"python3 scripts/quality-check.py 2>&1\"\n   387→    results = [success, fail]\n   388→  }\n   389→\n   390→  step fix {\n   391→    prompt = file(\"prompts/fix.md\")\n   392→    max_attempts = \"2\"\n   393→    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   394→  }\n   395→\n   396→  implement:success -> test\n   397→  implement:fail -> abort\n   398→\n   399→  test:success -> lint\n   400→  test:success -> quality\n   401→  test:fail -> fix\n   402→\n   403→  lint:fail -> fix\n   404→  quality:fail -> fix\n   405→  collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   406→\n   407→  fix:success -> test\n   408→  fix:fail -> abort\n   409→  fix:give-up -> abort\n   410→}\n   411→```\n   412→\n   413→## Container Isolation Model\n   414→\n   415→- **Files in**: `docker cp` copies the project into `/workspace/`. No bind mounts. Override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on top. `.git/` is included.\n   416→- **Files out**: On completion, the daemon extracts results via `docker cp` into a git worktree and commits to a `cloche/<run-id>` branch.\n   417→- **Auth mounts**: `~/.claude` and `~/.claude.json` are bind-mounted read-only for Claude Code session reuse.\n   418→- **Network**: Containers have network access (needed for API calls).\n   419→- **Cleanup**: Containers are removed after successful runs unless `--keep-container` is set. Failed runs always keep their container.\n   420→\n   421→Your project directory is never modified by the container.\n   422→\n   423→## CLI Reference\n   424→\n   425→### `cloche init`\n   426→\n   427→Scaffold a new Cloche project.\n   428→\n   429→```\n   430→cloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <base>]\n   431→```\n   432→\n   433→| Flag | Default | Description |\n   434→|------|---------|-------------|\n   435→| `--workflow <name>` | `develop` | Workflow name. Creates `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n   436→| `--base-image <base>` | `cloche-base:latest` | Base Docker image for the generated Dockerfile. |\n   437→\n   438→Creates `.cloche/` with workflow file, Dockerfile, `config.toml`, prompt templates,\n   439→host workflow (`host.cloche`), and prompt generation script. Skips existing files.\n   440→\n   441→### `cloche run`\n   442→\n   443→Launch a workflow run.\n   444→\n   445→```\n   446→cloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n   447→```\n   448→\n   449→| Flag | Description |\n   450→|------|-------------|\n   451→| `--workflow <name>` | Workflow name. Resolves to `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n   452→| `--prompt \"...\"`, `-p` | Inline prompt written to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`. |\n   453→| `--title \"...\"` | One-line summary for status display. Auto-generated if omitted. |\n   454→| `--keep-container` | Keep container on success (failed runs always keep it). |\n   455→\n   456→Must be run from inside a git repository. The daemon auto-rebuilds the Docker image\n   457→when `.cloche/Dockerfile` changes.\n   458→\n   459→### `cloche status`\n   460→\n   461→```\n   462→cloche status <run-id>\n   463→```\n   464→\n   465→Shows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and per-step results.\n   466→\n   467→### `cloche list`\n   468→\n   469→```\n   470→cloche list [--all]\n   471→```\n   472→\n   473→Lists runs for the current project directory. Pass `--all` to show runs across all projects.\n   474→\n   475→### `cloche logs`\n   476→\n   477→```\n   478→cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f]\n   479→```\n   480→\n   481→| Flag | Description |\n   482→|------|-------------|\n   483→| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n   484→| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n   485→| `-f` | Follow mode: display existing logs then continue streaming new lines as they arrive (like `tail -f`). |\n   486→\n   487→Without `-f`, displays all logs captured to date and exits (even for active runs). With `-f` on an active run, existing logs are sent first, then new output is streamed in real time via gRPC until the run completes.\n   488→\n   489→### `cloche poll`\n   490→\n   491→```\n   492→cloche poll <run-id>\n   493→```\n   494→\n   495→Block until the run finishes. Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 on success, 1 on failure.\n   496→\n   497→### `cloche stop`\n   498→\n   499→```\n   500→cloche stop <run-id>\n   501→```\n   502→\n   503→### `cloche delete`\n   504→\n   505→```\n   506→cloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n   507→```\n   508→\n   509→Delete a retained Docker container by container ID or run ID.\n   510→\n   511→### `cloche health`\n   512→\n   513→```\n   514→cloche health\n   515→```\n   516→\n   517→Show per-project pass/fail summary. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`.\n   518→\n   519→### `cloche get`\n   520→\n   521→```\n   522→cloche get <key>\n   523→```\n   524→\n   525→Get a value from the run context store (`.cloche/<run-id>/context.json`). Requires\n   526→the `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` environment variable. Uses `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` if set, otherwise\n   527→the current working directory. Exits 1 if the key is not found.\n   528→\n   529→### `cloche set`\n   530→\n   531→```\n   532→cloche set <key> <value|->\n   533→```\n   534→\n   535→Set a value in the run context store (`.cloche/<run-id>/context.json`). Requires\n   536→the `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` environment variable. Uses `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` if set, otherwise\n   537→the current working directory. Creates the file and directories if they don't exist.\n   538→Pass `-` as the value to read from stdin (trailing newlines are trimmed).\n   539→\n   540→### `cloche tasks`\n   541→\n   542→```\n   543→cloche tasks [--project <dir>]\n   544→```\n   545→\n   546→Show the task pipeline and assignment state for an orchestration loop. Displays\n   547→upcoming/open tasks, which tasks are assigned to which runs, and auto-assignment\n   548→state. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP` (talks to the daemon's web API).\n   549→\n   550→| Flag | Default | Description |\n   551→|------|---------|-------------|\n   552→| `--project <dir>` | current directory name | Project to query tasks for. |\n   553→\n   554→### `cloche shutdown`\n   555→\n   556→```\n   557→cloche shutdown\n   558→```\n   559→\n   560→## Project Layout\n   561→\n   562→```\n   563→my-project/\n   564→├── .cloche/\n   565→│   ├── develop.cloche        # Container workflow\n   566→│   ├── host.cloche           # Host orchestration workflow\n   567→│   ├── Dockerfile            # Container image definition\n   568→│   ├── config.toml           # Project configuration\n   569→│   ├── prompts/              # Prompt templates\n   570→│   │   ├── implement.md\n   571→│   │   ├── fix.md\n   572→│   │   └── update-docs.md\n   573→│   ├── scripts/              # Host-side scripts\n   574→│   ├── overrides/            # Files copied on top of /workspace/\n   575→│   │   └── CLAUDE.md         # Container-specific CLAUDE.md (optional)\n   576→│   └── <run-id>/             # Runtime state (gitignored)\n   577→│       ├── prompt.txt        # User prompt\n   578→│       ├── context.json      # Shared key-value store (cloche get/set)\n   579→│       ├── output/\n   580→│       │   ├── full.log      # Unified log\n   581→│       │   ├── test.log      # Per-step script output\n   582→│       │   └── llm-impl.log  # Per-step LLM conversation\n   583→│       ├── attempt_count/    # Retry counters for max_attempts\n   584→│       └── history.log       # Step execution log\n   585→├── src/                      # Project source (untouched by Cloche)\n   586→└── .git/\n   587→```\n   588→\n   589→## Daemon Configuration\n   590→\n   591→| Variable | Default | Description |\n   592→|----------|---------|-------------|\n   593→| `CLOCHE_LISTEN` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Listen address |\n   594→| `CLOCHE_DB` | `cloche.db` | SQLite database path |\n   595→| `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` | `docker` | `docker` or `local` (subprocess, for dev only) |\n   596→| `CLOCHE_IMAGE` | `cloche-agent:latest` | Default Docker image |\n   597→| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | _(unset)_ | HTTP address for web dashboard. Not started unless set. |\n   598→| `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` | _(auto)_ | Path to `cloche-agent` binary (local runtime) |\n   599→| `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` | _(unset)_ | Command for LLM calls (evolution, merge conflicts) |\n   600→| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | _(unset)_ | Passed into Docker containers |\n   601→| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` | _(unset)_ | Extra bind mounts (comma-separated `host:container`) |\n   602→| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` | _(unset)_ | Extra env vars (comma-separated `KEY=VALUE`) |\n   603→\n   604→### Client Configuration\n   605→\n   606→| Variable | Default | Description |\n   607→|----------|---------|-------------|\n   608→| `CLOCHE_ADDR` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Daemon gRPC address |\n   609→| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | `localhost:8080` | Daemon HTTP address |\n   610→\n   611→## Dockerfile Requirements\n   612→\n   613→The container image must have:\n   614→- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n   615→- `git` installed\n   616→- An `agent` user (cloche wraps commands with `chown` + `su agent`)\n   617→- `/workspace` as the working directory\n   618→- Your project's build dependencies and the agent binary (e.g. `claude`)\n   619→\n   620→## Build Commands\n   621→\n   622→```\n   623→make build          # Build all binaries to bin/\n   624→make test           # Run all tests\n   625→make test-short     # Run tests (skip slow ones)\n   626→make lint           # Run go vet\n   627→make proto          # Regenerate gRPC code from protobuf\n   628→make docker-build   # Build the cloche-agent Docker image\n   629→make install        # Build, install to ~/.local/bin/, restart daemon\n   630→make clean          # Remove bin/\n   631→```\n   632→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JL8mFVY8Rhg22KuPsWEiLJ","session_id":"6b861655-1988-46e5-92b9-f0a2db90f2de","uuid":"ad9ab90f-2cb3-4214-a1de-a25b070c3a0d"}
