[2026-03-13T14:37:10Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01By3FB9wsdvD9SNNKmKQDjD","type":"tool_result","content":"    60→## Step Types\n    61→\n    62→Step type is inferred from the fields present in the step body:\n    63→\n    64→**agent** (has `prompt`) — Invokes a coding agent (Claude Code, or any tool conforming\n    65→to the agent adapter interface) with a prompt. The agent works autonomously inside the\n    66→container. Available in both host and container workflows.\n    67→\n    68→**script** (has `run`) — Runs a shell command. Used for tests, linters, validators, or\n    69→any deterministic check. Available in both host and container workflows.\n    70→\n    71→**workflow** (has `workflow_name`) — Dispatches a named container workflow run and blocks\n    72→until it completes. Only available in host workflows (`host.cloche`).\n    73→\n    74→A step with more than one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`, or none of them, is a\n    75→parse error.\n    76→\n    77→## DSL Syntax\n    78→\n    79→```\n    80→workflow \"develop\" {\n    81→  container {\n    82→    image = \"my-project:latest\"\n    83→    agent_command = \"claude\"\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  step implement {\n    87→    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    88→    results = [success, fail]\n    89→  }\n    90→\n    91→  step test {\n    92→    run = \"make test && make lint\"\n    93→    results = [success, fail]\n    94→  }\n    95→\n    96→  step fix {\n    97→    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n    98→    max_attempts = \"3\"\n    99→    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   100→  }\n   101→\n   102→  // Wiring: step:result -> next_step [optional output mappings]\n   103→  implement:success -> test\n   104→  implement:fail    -> abort\n   105→  test:success      -> done\n   106→  test:fail         -> fix\n   107→  fix:success       -> test\n   108→  fix:fail          -> abort\n   109→  fix:give-up       -> abort\n   110→}\n   111→```\n   112→\n   113→## Key Properties\n   114→\n   115→**Step type is inferred from content.** A `prompt` field makes it an agent step; a `run`\n   116→field makes it a script step.\n   117→\n   118→**Steps declare their possible results.** A step decides at runtime which result to\n   119→report. The graph engine follows the wiring to determine the next step.\n   120→\n   121→**Wiring is separate from step definitions.** This enables inserting new steps between\n   122→existing ones by rewiring — without modifying either step. This is the foundation for\n   123→Cloche's self-evolution feature.\n   124→\n   125→**Graphs are validated at parse time.** The parser checks that all declared results are\n   126→wired, no steps are orphaned, and an entry point exists.\n   127→\n   128→## Wire Output Mappings\n   129→\n   130→Wires can include output mappings that extract values from a step's output and inject\n   131→them as environment variables into the target step:\n   132→\n   133→```\n   134→step-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n   135→```\n   136→\n   137→The general form:\n   138→\n   139→```"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6b861655-1988-46e5-92b9-f0a2db90f2de","uuid":"35ed3aa2-5b71-460b-81be-33b6bb9decdf","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/workflows.md","content":"## Step Types\n\nStep type is inferred from the fields present in the step body:\n\n**agent** (has `prompt`) — Invokes a coding agent (Claude Code, or any tool conforming\nto the agent adapter interface) with a prompt. The agent works autonomously inside the\ncontainer. Available in both host and container workflows.\n\n**script** (has `run`) — Runs a shell command. Used for tests, linters, validators, or\nany deterministic check. Available in both host and container workflows.\n\n**workflow** (has `workflow_name`) — Dispatches a named container workflow run and blocks\nuntil it completes. Only available in host workflows (`host.cloche`).\n\nA step with more than one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`, or none of them, is a\nparse error.\n\n## DSL Syntax\n\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  container {\n    image = \"my-project:latest\"\n    agent_command = \"claude\"\n  }\n\n  step implement {\n    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step test {\n    run = \"make test && make lint\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step fix {\n    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n    max_attempts = \"3\"\n    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n  }\n\n  // Wiring: step:result -> next_step [optional output mappings]\n  implement:success -> test\n  implement:fail    -> abort\n  test:success      -> done\n  test:fail         -> fix\n  fix:success       -> test\n  fix:fail          -> abort\n  fix:give-up       -> abort\n}\n```\n\n## Key Properties\n\n**Step type is inferred from content.** A `prompt` field makes it an agent step; a `run`\nfield makes it a script step.\n\n**Steps declare their possible results.** A step decides at runtime which result to\nreport. The graph engine follows the wiring to determine the next step.\n\n**Wiring is separate from step definitions.** This enables inserting new steps between\nexisting ones by rewiring — without modifying either step. This is the foundation for\nCloche's self-evolution feature.\n\n**Graphs are validated at parse time.** The parser checks that all declared results are\nwired, no steps are orphaned, and an entry point exists.\n\n## Wire Output Mappings\n\nWires can include output mappings that extract values from a step's output and inject\nthem as environment variables into the target step:\n\n```\nstep-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n```\n\nThe general form:\n\n```","numLines":80,"startLine":60,"totalLines":274}}}
[2026-03-13T14:37:10Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HjTkx7yAaQibnh8kp5LbQy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01VrnyiP8QZZhwzR8aRuSFNu","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md","offset":60,"limit":120},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2157,"cache_read_input_tokens":19454,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2157},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6b861655-1988-46e5-92b9-f0a2db90f2de","uuid":"dcd00ba1-55d8-4d29-816b-04ff97262c6c"}
[2026-03-13T14:37:10Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VrnyiP8QZZhwzR8aRuSFNu","type":"tool_result","content":"    60→### The `file()` Function\n    61→\n    62→`file(\"path\")` reads the file at the given path relative to the working directory\n    63→(`/workspace/` in containers) at execution time, not parse time. Use it for prompt\n    64→templates:\n    65→\n    66→```\n    67→prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    68→```\n    69→\n    70→### The `container {}` Block\n    71→\n    72→Can appear at step level or workflow level. Keys are stored with a `container.` prefix.\n    73→\n    74→**Step level** — per-step container config:\n    75→```\n    76→step code {\n    77→  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    78→  container {\n    79→    image         = \"custom-agent:v2\"\n    80→    memory        = \"4g\"\n    81→    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n    82→  }\n    83→  results = [success, fail]\n    84→}\n    85→```\n    86→\n    87→**Workflow level** — defaults for all steps:\n    88→```\n    89→workflow \"develop\" {\n    90→  container {\n    91→    agent_command = \"gemini\"\n    92→    image         = \"myregistry/myimage:v2\"\n    93→    memory        = \"4g\"\n    94→  }\n    95→  ...\n    96→}\n    97→```\n    98→\n    99→Supported keys: `image`, `memory`, `network_allow`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`.\n   100→\n   101→### The `host {}` Block\n   102→\n   103→Can appear at workflow level in host workflows (`.cloche/host.cloche`). Keys are stored\n   104→with a `host.` prefix. Configures agent defaults for agent steps running on the host.\n   105→\n   106→```\n   107→workflow \"main\" {\n   108→  host {\n   109→    agent_command = \"claude\"\n   110→  }\n   111→  ...\n   112→}\n   113→```\n   114→\n   115→Supported keys: `agent_command`, `agent_args`. Step-level `agent_command` and\n   116→`agent_args` config keys override the workflow-level `host {}` defaults.\n   117→\n   118→### Wiring Syntax\n   119→\n   120→Connect steps with `step:result -> next_step`:\n   121→\n   122→```\n   123→implement:success -> test\n   124→implement:fail -> abort\n   125→test:success -> done\n   126→test:fail -> fix\n   127→```\n   128→\n   129→### Wire Output Mappings\n   130→\n   131→Extract values from a step's JSON output and inject as env vars into the target:\n   132→\n   133→```\n   134→step-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n   135→```\n   136→\n   137→Path expressions:\n   138→\n   139→| Expression | Meaning |\n   140→|---|---|\n   141→| `output` | Raw output (full string) |\n   142→| `output.key` | JSON object field access |\n   143→| `output[N]` | JSON array index (0-based) |\n   144→| `output.a.b.c` | Deeply nested field access |\n   145→| `output.items[0].name` | Mixed field and index chaining |\n   146→\n   147→If the output is valid JSON, path expressions navigate the structure. If it's plain\n   148→text, only bare `output` works.\n   149→\n   150→### Retry Loops\n   151→\n   152→Wire failures back to earlier steps:\n   153→\n   154→```\n   155→test:fail -> fix\n   156→fix:success -> test    // retry the test\n   157→fix:fail -> abort\n   158→```\n   159→\n   160→Use `max_attempts` to cap retries. When exhausted, the step returns `give-up`:\n   161→\n   162→```\n   163→step fix {\n   164→  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n   165→  max_attempts = \"2\"\n   166→  results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   167→}\n   168→```\n   169→\n   170→### Parallel Branches (Fanout)\n   171→\n   172→Wire one result to multiple targets for concurrent execution:\n   173→\n   174→```\n   175→test:success -> lint\n   176→test:success -> quality\n   177→```\n   178→\n   179→### Collect (Join)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6b861655-1988-46e5-92b9-f0a2db90f2de","uuid":"5030be8c-8306-43bf-a9ca-d6760b0de360","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md","content":"### The `file()` Function\n\n`file(\"path\")` reads the file at the given path relative to the working directory\n(`/workspace/` in containers) at execution time, not parse time. Use it for prompt\ntemplates:\n\n```\nprompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n```\n\n### The `container {}` Block\n\nCan appear at step level or workflow level. Keys are stored with a `container.` prefix.\n\n**Step level** — per-step container config:\n```\nstep code {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n  container {\n    image         = \"custom-agent:v2\"\n    memory        = \"4g\"\n    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n  }\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\n**Workflow level** — defaults for all steps:\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  container {\n    agent_command = \"gemini\"\n    image         = \"myregistry/myimage:v2\"\n    memory        = \"4g\"\n  }\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nSupported keys: `image`, `memory`, `network_allow`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`.\n\n### The `host {}` Block\n\nCan appear at workflow level in host workflows (`.cloche/host.cloche`). Keys are stored\nwith a `host.` prefix. Configures agent defaults for agent steps running on the host.\n\n```\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  host {\n    agent_command = \"claude\"\n  }\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nSupported keys: `agent_command`, `agent_args`. Step-level `agent_command` and\n`agent_args` config keys override the workflow-level `host {}` defaults.\n\n### Wiring Syntax\n\nConnect steps with `step:result -> next_step`:\n\n```\nimplement:success -> test\nimplement:fail -> abort\ntest:success -> done\ntest:fail -> fix\n```\n\n### Wire Output Mappings\n\nExtract values from a step's JSON output and inject as env vars into the target:\n\n```\nstep-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n```\n\nPath expressions:\n\n| Expression | Meaning |\n|---|---|\n| `output` | Raw output (full string) |\n| `output.key` | JSON object field access |\n| `output[N]` | JSON array index (0-based) |\n| `output.a.b.c` | Deeply nested field access |\n| `output.items[0].name` | Mixed field and index chaining |\n\nIf the output is valid JSON, path expressions navigate the structure. If it's plain\ntext, only bare `output` works.\n\n### Retry Loops\n\nWire failures back to earlier steps:\n\n```\ntest:fail -> fix\nfix:success -> test    // retry the test\nfix:fail -> abort\n```\n\nUse `max_attempts` to cap retries. When exhausted, the step returns `give-up`:\n\n```\nstep fix {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n  max_attempts = \"2\"\n  results = [success, fail, give-up]\n}\n```\n\n### Parallel Branches (Fanout)\n\nWire one result to multiple targets for concurrent execution:\n\n```\ntest:success -> lint\ntest:success -> quality\n```\n\n### Collect (Join)","numLines":120,"startLine":60,"totalLines":632}}}
